Atlanta Family Law and Divorce Attorneys

Dynamic and Experienced Attorneys in Family and Divorce Legal Services

TDE Family Law & Divorce Attorneys is an experienced family law firm that has been serving the Atlanta, GA community for over 15 years. Our attorneys provide enthusiastic representation and bring along extensive experience in representing our clients. We strive to provide personalized, affordable legal services with special discounts for military personnel and first responders.

$100 Consultation Fee
$50 Military/ First Responders (valid ID required)
All consultation fees are applied to the initial retainer if retained within 7 days of consultation.

Georgia Divorce & Family Law Services

Divorce

Turn to our experienced attorneys to represent your divorce case. Were efficient at assisting our clients with contested or uncontested divorce, asset division, custody and more.

Learn More

Child Support & Custody

Get the right guidance you need when it comes to legal modifications. Well assist you with modifying primary or joint physical custody, visitation, and other parenting time agreements.

Learn More

Contempt

When the court orders someone to do (or stop doing) something and that person ignores the order, they are considered to be in contempt of court.

Learn More

Fathers Rights

Whether you are trying to establish your rights as a father or want to protect those rights in divorce, you need to work within the legal rules that apply to family law matters in Georgia.

Learn More

Uncontested Divorce

Uncontested divorce provides the fastest and least expensive way to dissolve a marriage, but the process may still not be as simple as you expect.

Learn More

Legitimation

Turn to our experienced attorneys to represent your divorce case. Were efficient at assisting our clients with contested or uncontested divorce, asset division, custody and more.
Learn More

Modifications

There are instances when change takes place and the need to modify agreements arises. Let the experienced attorneys at TDE Family Law & Divorce Attorneys assist you with every aspect of change, whether it is a financial shift, child support, visitation, or other needs.

Learn More

Paternity

Under Georgia law, parents have legal rights and responsibilities with respect to their children. However, in many cases, legal action is necessary to take advantage of the rights and enforce the responsibilities and proving paternity is a good first step.

Learn More

Temporary/ Emergency Protective Orders

Temporary protective orders are your legal recourse to tell someone to stay away from you and your loved ones. Each state has its own laws regarding these orders and knowing Georgia laws can help you understand how to obtain one.
Learn More

My husband used this firm to represent him in an effort to obtain parental rights and custody for his daughter from a previous relationship. This matter was extremely important to us both in order to establish parenting time as soon as possible. It really felt like they were either over stretched in case loads, dragged their feet, and would overlook important details. Errors were made that set us back months. We are a faith based family who prayed long and hard for good counsel before deciding on them. Unfortunately it took us nearly a year to realize that wed made a mistake. We eventually left this firm after acquiring over $27,000 in legal fees by the 60 day hearing of the custody case. We did not feel as though they stewarded the funds that we deposited into the billing trust responsibly and instead would find creative ways of billing at high rates. Things like having two attorneys log into the same uneventful virtual hearing so they could both bill, and without my husbands consent. Or speaking to opposing counsel for nearly 2 hours for a cost of $950 just to discuss visitation details. It seems like an email would have been more appropriate. Billing for long calls of this nature were common and quickly exhausted the bulk of our funds. Huge administrative mistakes were made and wed go weeks to months without updates. When my husband would reach out for updates hed be billed for inquiring (email, call, etc).

They will ask you to upload pertinent evidence into their online portal but you will quickly realize that its seldom read by anyone aside from the administrative staff. My husband would spend countless hours preparing evidence only to receive duplicate request for evidence that hed already uploaded in the preceding months. This was frustrating, emotionally draining, and ultimately amounted to extremely expensive insufficient representation. God is still advocating for us and we are believing that this financial set back will not prevent us from uniting with our child. God is bigger than financial exploitation and we will overcome this. With that being said, I would not recommend this firm to anyone and wish that wed moved on from them sooner.
